comments: Adams (MEM) establishes himself in Reddish's (NYK) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Brunson (NYK) exits the paint within three seconds.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) is in the paint for three seconds when he moves to imminently guard Robinson (NYK).
Adams (MEM) gives a step of distance when establishing himself in Reddish's (NYK) path and marginal contact occurs during the pick.
Robinson (NYK) initiates contact with Morant's (MEM) right arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Adams (MEM) and Barrett (NYK) engage and disengage with one another, and marginal contact occurs during the free throw attempt.
Morant (MEM) is in the paint for three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Adams (MEM) is in the paint for three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Morant (MEM) touches the ball last before it goes OOB.
Konchar (MEM) and Robinson (NYK) engage and disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Konchar (MEM) moves alongside Barrett's (NYK) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.

Adams (MEM) and Robinson (NYK) pursue the loose ball, and marginal contact with Robinson's head occurs during the rebound. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Morant (MEM) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.

Replay review of the foul called on Brooks (MEM) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Brooks initiates foot to foot contact with Brunson (NYK) that dislodges him from his position during the drive.
Barrett (NYK) retreats in Morant's (MEM) path and maintains verticality as he absorbs the contact that occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Robinson (NYK) cleanly blocks the ball during Morant's (MEM) driving shot attempt.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) grasps and then quickly releases Reddish's (NYK) jersey during the in-bounds play.
Grimes (NYK) commits a take foul on Morant (MEM).
Robinson (NYK) and Adams (MEM) mutually engage and immediately disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Adams (MEM) and Randle (NYK) engage for rebounding position during the free throw attempt and marginal contact occurs.
Barrett (NYK) releases the in-bounds pass within five seconds.
Clarke (MEM) briefly rests a hand on Brunson's (NYK) side before retracting it during the driving shot attempt.
Brunson (NYK) commits a take foul on Jackson Jr. (MEM).
